inter bonos] The Caesars en- joyed general admiration, while both their generosity or policy and the natural tradition of the aristo- cracy combined to prevent respect· able people from condemning the Republican champions. imperium . . . rem p.] One must translate ‘the Empire' and ‘ the Republic ' (cf. note on i. 1. 2), but both the Latin words have dignified associations which the English have not.
